<HEAD>With PM-Clean Air</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are the counties that the Environmental
Protection Agency says must be considered part of areas that fail
to meet federal air quality standards for carbon monoxide.
   This list shows only entire counties. There are a few counties
not listed where part of the county has been excluded from the
planning area and the entire county must now be considered.
   In the Virginia listing, the entries are counties unless
specified as a city. Where the county includes the word ``city'' as
part of the name, the word ``county'' is added.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   Arkansas: Crittenden.
   California: Ventura, Yolo.
   Colorado: Douglas.
   Connecticut: New London.
   Illinois: Clinton, Jersey, Madison, Monroe, St. Clair.
