<HEAD>Stocks Down, Dollar Gains Slightly</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: LEADS with 3 grafs to UPDATE with closing stock and dollar
figures. PICKS up 4th graf, ``Some (industry) ...'</NOTE>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices fell in Tokyo trading Friday while the
U.S. dollar gained slightly against the yen.
   The dollar closed at 124.64 yen in Tokyo Friday, up 0.14 yen
from Thursday's finish.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Average index of 225
selected issues finished Friday at 27,290.49 points, down 137.75
points, or 0.50 percent, from Thursday's closing figure.
   ``Some (industry) sectors are taking a rest,'' said Yoshio
Shimoyama, a trader with Nikko Securities. ``The Nikkei (average)
is often a bit weak toward the end of the month.''
   Japanese Finance Minister Kiichi Miyazawa welcomed Thursday's
announcement of a strong upward revision in the growth of the U.S.
economy in the first three months of the year, to 3.9 percent.
   The GNP report, however, failed to stimulate currency trading in
New York Thursday and only slightly boosted the dollar on the Tokyo
foreign-exchange market, dealers said.
   They said currency market participants welcomed the reported
decline in the U.S. inflation rate from 2.4 percent last year to
1.7 percent during the first quarter of this year.
