<HEAD>Cargo Plane Crashes, Pilot and Co-Pilot Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HANOVER, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A twin-propeller Danish cargo plane
crashed and exploded near Hanover's airport, killing the pilot and
co-pilot, police said today.
   The Fokker 27 crashed late Thursday while approaching the
airport for a scheduled stop, police said. They said the pilot and
co-pilot, the only people abord, were apparently Danes.
   The airplane, on its way to Nuremberg from Billund, Denmark,
crashed in an uninhabited area about a mile from the airport and
exploded when it hit the ground, police said.
   Police said the crash is being investigated by local air
authorities who have not yet determined the cause.
   Further information was not immediately available.
