<HEAD>Thunderstorms Linger In Minnesota, the Dakotas</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   A band of showers and thunderstorms lingered in Minnesota and
the Dakotas today, whipping up winds and pelting some areas with
hail.
   The storm system extended Thursday night from central Minnesota
into southeastern North Dakota. In North Dakota, winds gusted to 62
mph in Fargo, while McLeod and areas near Christine reported 60 mph
winds.
   Hail an inch in diameter hit Onaka, S.D., and Rothsay, Minn.
   Widely scattered showers and a few thundershowers were reported
in the Rockies, eastern Nebraska and northern Texas. In Price,
Utah, windows and a large sign were damaged by wind gusts of 60 mph
during a thunderstorm.
   Elsewhere, rain extended along the northern Pacific Coast. Dry
weather prevailed east of the Mississippi River and across the
southern Plains under mostly clear skies.
   Today's forecast called for thunderstorms in southern Florida;
widely scattered thunderstorms in the Rockies and High Plains;
showers and thunderstorms in upper Michigan and northern Wisconsin;
a few showers in Washington and northern Oregon; and sunny skies
across much of the rest of the nation.
   Temperatures around most of the nation were forecast in the 70s
or 80s; the 60s along the northern and central Pacific Coast; the
90s to around 100 degrees in the Rio Grande Valley and across the
desert Southwest.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 40
degrees at Houlton, Maine, and Yellowstone National Park, Wyo., to
88 degrees at Phoenix, Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 59 fair; Boston 52 fair; Buffalo 65 cloudy;
Charleston, S.C. 56 fair; Cincinnati 48 fair; Cleveland 54 fair;
Detroit 64 fair; Miami 74 partly cloudy; New York 58 fair;
Philadelphia 51 fair; Pittsburgh 52 partly cloudy; Portland, Maine
49 fair; Washington 53 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 54 fair; Chicago 60 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
61 fair; Denver 56 fair; Des Moines 62 partly cloudy; Indianapolis
50 fair; Kansas City 58 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 73 windy;
Nashville 52 fair; New Orleans 68 fair; St. Louis 62 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 66 windy; Anchorage 52 fair; Las Vegas 80
fair; Los Angeles 60 partly cloudy; Phoenix 88 fair; Salt Lake City
72 partly cloudy; San Diego 63 cloudy; San Francisco 56 cloudy;
Seattle 54 rain.
   _Canada: Montreal 59 cloudy; Toronto 55 fair.
</TEXT>
