<HEAD>Plane Makes Emergency Landing Following Bomb Threat</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NANTES, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Alitalia jumbo jet carrying about 400
passengers from New York to Milan made an emergency landing in
western France today after a caller said a bomb had been placed
aboard the plane, police said.
   An Alitalia source, speaking on condition of anonymity, said
seven people were slightly injured during the emergency evacuation
of the plane. No explosives were immediately found.
   The flight was over France when Alitalia officials in Milan
received the bomb threat. Within 20 minutes, Italian police had
contacted French authorities who instructed the plane to land. The
airliner touched down at 8:30 a.m. (2:30 a.m. EDT).
   The passengers, most of whom were American or Italian, were
expected to continue on another flight later today.
