<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Libya-US     05-27 0138</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Libya-US,0142</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Libya Claims U.S. Plane Buzzed Libyan Merchant Ship</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Libya's news agency claimed an American plane buzzed
a Libyan merchant ship in the Mediterranean near the Spanish coast.
The Pentagon said it knew of no such incident.
   The dispatch by the JANA news agency, monitored in Rome, said a
U.S. 6th Fleet plane flew low over the Libyan freighter Al-Jazair
Thursday afternoon when the ship was 62 miles from Cartagena, Spain.
   ``This provocative act threatens commercial navigation posing a
danger to commercial ships,'' JANA said.
   It added that Libya reserves the right to pursue the matter
before the appropriate international organizations.
   In Washington, Fred Hoffman, a Defense Department spokesman,
said late Thursday the Pentagon was unaware of the Libyan claim and
knew of no contacts involving a U.S. jet and Libyan merchant ship.
</TEXT>
