amount of advertising that may be shown during children's
television programs.
   The House Commerce and Energy Committee on Thursday voted 39-3
to send the measure to the House floor, where it is expected to win
approval.
   The bill passed by the House committee would limit TV stations
to no more than 10{ minutes of commercials per hour during
children's shows on weekends and 12 minutes per hour during these
programs on weekdays.
   The measure is a bipartisan compromise stripped of earlier
proposals to prohibit programs called ``program-length
commercials'' that are built around toy manufacturers' products.
Senate legislation on children's TV would bar these programs.
