<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Dartmouth Recruiting,0139</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dartmouth Says Fly-In Program For Top Scholars A Success</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HANOVER, N.H. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dartmouth College has doubled the number of
incoming top freshman students by flying in many of them for a VIP
tour of the campus, the school said Friday.
   Of the 201 top high school seniors targeted under the
Presidential Scholars program, 63 have picked Dartmouth _ double
its enrollment of top scholars last year, spokesman Alex Huppe said.
   Dartmouth also expects a record number of women in its freshman
class of 1,100. Applications from women were up 13 percent over
last year and this fall's class is expected to be 44 percent women,
up from 38 percent last year, Huppe said.
   The percentage of minority freshman will increase by 2 percent
to just more than 20 percent, the school said.
