<HEAD>Koch Has 5 Non-Cancerous Lesions Removed From His Face</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mayor Edward I. Koch had five non-cancerous
lesions removed from his face Friday morning.
   He said three were caused by exposure to the sun and the other
two were from an inherited condition.
   ``They are common and benign lesions,'' Koch said.
   He said he visited a dermatologist, Richard Green, who gave him
a local anesthetic and removed the lesions in about 20 minutes.
   He said no further medical treatment is required and that he has
been placed under no restrictions.
   He said he was advised to avoid prolonged exposure to the sun.
   ``I have always believed it is a good idea to follow doctor's
orders. But as we begin what promises to be a beautiful and bright
Memorial Day weekend, it may not be easy to do,'' he said.
