<2ND_LINE>AM-China-Family Planning,140</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>US Withholds Funds From UN Agency</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The United States is withholding $25 million
from a United Nations family planning agency because of its support
for a program in China which is alleged to use coercive population
control methods, it was announced Friday.
   The Agency for International Development said the funds will
earmarked for U.S.-backed programs in Africa, Asia and Latin
America.
   The United States first withheld funds from the U.N. Fund for
Population Activities in 1985 after concluding that the agency
participated in the management of a program in China which involved
coercive abortion and involuntary sterilization.
   AID administrator Alan Woods said that a review of the program
indicated that the ``significant changes that would warrant
resumption of support have not occurred.''
   The study was carried out by the Census Bureau's Center for
International Research.
</TEXT>
