<HEAD>GOP To Hold Unity Meeting In Denver</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Vice President George Bush and hundreds of Western
GOP leaders will meet here next month to show their support of the
party's presidential ticket and Republican candidates for other
offices.
   The event, which will begin June 10, is the first of four
planned by the Republican National Committee. Other such gatherings
will be in Boston, Chicago and Atlanta later this summer.
   Tom Hockaday, the Western regional political director for the
Bush campaign, said the purpose of the meeting is ``to bring
together not only the vice president but other (former)
presidential aspirants as well as to show we are all working
together to elect the vice president.''
   However, only one of the five former candidates _ Rep. Jack Kemp
of New York _ has said he will attend the two-day event.
   Spokeswomen for television evangelist Pat Robertson, former
Delaware Gov. Pete DuPont and Alexander Haig all said the former
candidates will not attend because of scheduling conflicts. Sen.
Bob Dole of Kansas has not decided whether to attend, a spokeswoman
for Dole said.
