<HEAD>Woman Arrested After Boyfriend's Dismembered Body Found in
Apartment</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Note contents may be offensive to some readers.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 26-year-old woman was arrested Friday after the
dismembered body of her boyfriend was found on the living room
floor of her north Capitol Hill apartment, police said.
   Lori McLuckie of Denver was jailed for investigation of
first-degree murder. The victim's identity was not released by
authorities.
   Detective Calvin Hemphill said police were called to the
apartment Friday on a tip and found the victim's torso and head on
a piece of plastic on the floor.
   A search turned up the victim's limbs, wrapped in plastic bags
and deposited in several dumpsters in the neighborhood.
   All body parts were found except for the victim's left foot and
a piece of his right thigh, Hemphill said.
   ``It looks like he may have been dead since last Saturday,''
Hemphill said.
   Police said they had found the tool used to carve up the body,
but they weren't saying what it was. The victim also showed signs
of multiple stab wounds, police said.
   Hemphill said McLuckie apparently had been carrying on her
normal routine and had continued living in the apartment since the
victim's death. She was roused from bed by police executing a
search warrant early Friday.
   A neighbor said he had noticed nothing unusual except for a foul
smell emanating from the apartment the last few days.
