<2ND_LINE>AM-Toy Recall, 3rd Ld-Writethru, a0866,210</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Playset and Doll Recalled</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDs: SUBS last graf to DELETE telephone number given for toy
company, which is apparently not working</NOTE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Sweet Home Shoe House playset and Ice Cream
Doll are being recalled nationwide because they may pose a choking
hazard to small children, the Consumer Product Safety Commission
announced Friday.
   About 6,500 of the Sweet Home Shoe House playsets were sold
across the country, the agency said. It described them as a plastic
house in the shape of a workboot, containing 18 pieces of dolls and
doll furniture. The set sold for about $5 and is labeled ``1984
Jumbos International (Hong Kong) Co. No. 698.''
   In addition, some 7,800 of the Ice Cream Doll were sold for
about $3 each, the commission said. These are soft dolls with a
plastic ice cream cone suspended around the neck. They are labeled
``Ice Cream Doll, Made in Hong Kong.''
   No injuries have been reported involving the toys, but both
contain small parts which could pose a choking hazard, the
commission said. Parents were urged to remove the toys from
children's use and to return them to the retailer for a refund.
   The toys were recalled by Wisconsin Toy Company Inc. of New
York, the commission said. Consumers needing more information may
call the Safety Commission at 1-800-638-2772.
</TEXT>
