<HEAD>Longworth Receives Trade Award</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Chicago World Trade Conference on Thursday
awarded its first journalism award for excellence in international
trade reporting to Chicago Tribune economics correspondent R. C.
Longworth.
   The World Trade Conference, held for the 50th time, is sponsored
by the International Trade Club of Chicago.
   Longworth, who joined the Tribune in 1976, was cited for his
reporting on the Japanese economy, the European Economic Community
and the Soviet economy.
   A graduate of Northwestern University, Longworth is scheduled to
