<DOCNO> AP880527-0320 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-05-27-88 1403EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r f BC-McGraw-HillSale     05-27 0137</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-McGraw-Hill Sale,0142</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>McGraw-Hill Sells Stake In Japanese Venture For $283 Million</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   McGraw-Hill Inc. said Friday it has sold its 49
percent interest in Nikkei-McGraw-Hill Inc., a joint venture
publishing company in Japan, for $283 million.
   The stake was bought by Nihon Keizai Shimbun, a major Japanese
publisher, which had owned 51 percent of the venture. The venture
publishes 16 magazines, six newsletters and other services in
Japanese.
   McGraw-Hill said it remained committed to doing business in
Japan. The company's Standard & Poor's unit recently established
operations in Tokyo.
   The sale gave McGraw-Hill a gain of $224 million before taxes
and $112 million after taxes, the company said. The gain will be
offset by write-downs in other assets and unusual charges amounting
to $149 million before taxes and $110 million after taxes.
</TEXT>
