<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices sagged today under the weight of
rising interest rates.
   After rising sharply on Thursday, interest rates moved up again
in the credit markets today.
   Analysts cited a spreading belief that the Federal Reserve was
tightening credit further in response to evidence of continuing
strength in the economy.
   On Thursday the Commerce Department made a sharp upward revision
in its figure for economic growth during the first quarter of the
year.
   Otherwise, brokers said, the market was suffering mainly from
neglect, with many participants getting an early start on the long
Memorial Day weekend.
