Ny $250,000 to thational Bank and Trust Co. of Prairie Village and $500,000
to the
Norbank of North Kansas City to make restitution for loans that he
obtained by making false financial statements.
   Kroh and his brother, John A. Kroh Jr., president of Kroh
Brothers Development, owned the prominent 77-year-old company that
developed shopping centers, residential areas and office buildings
across the country. The company entered bankruptcy proceedings in
