<1ST_LINE>r f AM-PeaSoup     05-27 0162</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Pea Soup,0169</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Nestle Recalls Crosse & Blackwell Cans</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PURCHASE, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nestle Foods Corp. announced Friday it was
voluntarily recalling all cans of Crosse & Blackwell split green
pea soup with ham.
   It asked that the product, which is distributed nationally, be
removed from all stores and warehouses and that individual
consumers return them to supermarkets for refund or replacement.
   Defects in some of the cans were detected by the company, which
then advised the federal Food and Drug Administration of the
recall, said Barbara Campbell, speaking for Nestle.
   She said the defect could cause cans to break and leak, which
would affect the product quality, but that no illness or injury has
been known to have occurred from the soup.
   The possibly defective cans are among 1,500 cases of the soup,
but as a precaution all cans of that type of soup were being
recalled, Nestle said.
   It said anyone with questions about the recall should call
800-553-5303.
</TEXT>
